                            <comment id="19739" author="ndeloof" created="Tue, 19 Sep 2006 02:17:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you consider this request as invalid, could you please enhance the doc to expose argumentation on rejecting field injection in the Spring doc please.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe field injection could be supported but marked as not beeing the privilegied injection mecanism ? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19893" author="ndeloof" created="Tue, 26 Sep 2006 05:55:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve noticed JPA support for @PersistenceUnit annotation allows field injection for EntityManager. Does this mean Spring ALLREADY supports field injection, without making this an explicit feature ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="76043" author="cbeams" created="Tue, 21 Feb 2012 02:40:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As discussed in the forum thread and elsewhere, field injection from XML is something that we won&apos;t be supporting in Spring Framework.  @Autowired and @Inject allow for this behavior for annotation-based components, but that&apos;s as far as we&apos;ll go.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
